    <article class="article">

      <header class="article-header">

        <h1 title="Scheduled maintenance " class="article-title">

          Scheduled maintenance 

          

        </h1>



        <div class="article-author">

          <div class="avatar article-avatar">

            

              <span class="icon-agent"></span>

            

            <img src="https://support.patreon.com/system/photos/0003/3137/3643/An_Open_Letter_to_Boring_Avatars_Everywhere___Meet_Foxes.png" alt="Avatar" class="user-avatar"/>

          </div>

          <div class="article-meta">

            

              Patreon Staff

            

   

          </div>

        </div>

        <a class="article-subscribe" title="Opens a sign-in dialog" rel="nofollow" role="button" data-auth-action="signin" aria-selected="false" href="/hc/en-us/articles/207995166-Scheduled-maintenance-/subscription">Follow</a>

      </header>



      <section class="article-info">

        <div class="article-content">

          <div class="article-body"><p>Every now and then, we need to do some maintenance to Patreon.com that requires us to take the site down for a short period of time. Prior to scheduled maintenance, Patreon will give advance notice.</p>

<p>If you are unsure if the maintenance is related to scheduled cleanup or a site-wide issue, check our support twitter account: <a href="https://twitter.com/PatreonSupport" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">@PatreonSupport</a></p>

<p>If our support twitter is reporting that we are back up and you still see a maintenance window, try clearing your browser cache. You can test if it's just you or everyone by visiting Patreon.com in private/incognito mode as well.</p></div>



